# Citus Marketing SEO

Every page must be indexable, shareable, and structurally sound. SEO is not optional on a marketing site.

## Site Configuration

Single source of truth: `config/site.ts`

Update once: `name`, `description`, `url`, `ogImage`, `keywords`.

All metadata helpers read from this file ŌĆö never hardcode site name or URL in page components.

## Per-Page Metadata (required)

Every route under `app/` exports metadata via `generateSEO()` from `@/lib/seo`:

```ts
import { generateSEO } from "@/lib/seo"

export const metadata = generateSEO({
  title: "Page Title",       // Ōēż ~50 chars (before `| Site Name` suffix)
  description: "...",        // 150ŌĆō160 chars, unique per page
  url: "/about/",            // trailing slash ŌĆö matches next.config trailingSlash
  keywords: ["optional"],    // page-specific keywords merged with siteConfig.keywords
})
```

`generateSEO()` provides: title, description, OpenGraph, Twitter card, canonical (`alternates.canonical`), and robots directives.

Root layout (`app/layout.tsx`) already sets `metadataBase`, `title.template`, default OG, and robots. Extend at page level ŌĆö do not duplicate globals.

## On-Page Structure

- **One `<h1>` per page** ŌĆö matches the page's primary intent and metadata title.
- Logical heading hierarchy: `h2` ŌåÆ `h3`. Never skip levels.
- **Images:** every `<Image />` needs meaningful `alt` text. OG images are 1200├Ś630 (`siteConfig.ogImage` ŌåÆ `/public/opengraph-image.png`).
- **Internal links:** descriptive anchor text ("View pricing plans"), not "click here".
- **`lang="en"`** on `<html>` (already set in layout).

## Semantic HTML

Use landmarks, not div soup:

```tsx
<header>...</header>
<main id="main-content">...</main>
<footer>...</footer>
```

Section content inside `<section>` with optional `id` for anchor links (e.g. `id="features"`).

## Structured Data (JSON-LD)

Global `WebSite` schema lives in `lib/schema.ts` and is injected in `app/layout.tsx`.

Extend `lib/schema.ts` with page-specific schemas when relevant:
- `Organization` ŌĆö homepage
- `FAQPage` ŌĆö FAQ sections
- `BreadcrumbList` ŌĆö nested pages

Inject page-specific JSON-LD in the page or layout `<head>`:

```tsx
<script
  type="application/ld+json"
  dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: JSON.stringify(mySchema) }}
/>
```

## New Route Checklist

When adding a page under `app/`:

1. Export `metadata` via `generateSEO()` with unique title, description, canonical URL
2. Add `loading.tsx` sibling for instant skeleton (zero layout shift)
3. Add URL entry to `app/sitemap.ts` with `changeFrequency` and `priority`
4. Ensure `app/robots.ts` sitemap reference remains valid (already points to sitemap)
5. One `<h1>`, logical heading tree, all images have `alt`

## Static SEO Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `app/sitemap.ts` | Lists all indexable URLs (`force-static`) |
| `app/robots.ts` | Allow indexing, reference sitemap |
| `app/manifest.webmanifest` | PWA manifest |
| `public/opengraph-image.png` | Default OG image (1200├Ś630) |

## NEVER

- Pages without `export const metadata`
- Duplicate or missing canonical URLs
- Multiple `<h1>` elements per page
- Missing `alt` on content images
- `noIndex: true` on public marketing pages (unless explicitly requested)
- Hardcoded `https://example.com` ŌĆö always use `siteConfig.url`
